Return Value","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A reducer that combines the child reducer with the parent reducer."}]}],"kind":"content"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if a parent feature holds onto an array of child states, then it can perform"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"its core logic "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the child’s logic by using the "},{"code":"forEach","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Parent {","  struct State {","    var rows: IdentifiedArrayOf<Row.State>","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    case rows(IdentifiedActionOf<Row>)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some Reducer<State, Action> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core logic for parent feature","    }","    .forEach(\\.rows, action: \\.rows) {","      Row()","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"aside","style":"tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We are using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"IdentifiedArray"},{"text":" from our","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-identified-collections","type":"reference"},{"text":" library because it provides a safe","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and ergonomic API for accessing elements from a stable ID rather than positional indices."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Tip"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"forEach"},{"type":"text","text":" forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features. It"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"runs the child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"possible for the parent feature to remove the child state from the array, in which case the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"child feature would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is still possible for a parent feature higher up in the application to remove the child","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"state from the array before the child has a chance to react to the action. In such cases a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"runtime warning is shown in Xcode to let you know that there’s a potential problem."}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/reducer\/foreach(_:action:element:fileid:filepath:line:column:)-6zye8"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/forEach(_:action:element:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-6zye8"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Identifying actions","anchor":"Identifying-actions","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/IdentifiedAction"]},{"anchor":"Navigation-stacks","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackState","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackActionOf","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/forEach(_:action:destination:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-9svqb","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/forEach(_:action:)","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/DismissEffect"],"title":"Nav